description.plain:
Ryan Mitchel Chassels (born September 19, 1997), better known as Freddie Dredd, is a Canadian rapper and producer based in Oshawa, Ontario. He is originally from Durham, Ontario.

Best known for blending gritty, lo-fi sounds, vintage samples, and intense—often dark—lyrics.
Despite this, Freddie’s albeit unique style started gaining traction in early 2019 after several of his songs became viral hits on the short-form mobile video app, TikTok.

In addition to his solo work, Freddie frequently collaborates with other underground hip-hop artists, such as Baker, RAMIREZ, and Slim Guerilla. He is also an active member of DoomshopRecords and SIXSET.

songs.title: Cha Cha

description.plain:
“Cha Cha” by Canadian rapper Freddie Dredd (also known as producer Ryan C.) is a lo-fi sensation which gained popularity primarily from the 15-second music-video app TikTok.

This single samples Japanese-Brazilian bossa nova singer Lisa Ono’s 2001 track “Sway it, Hula Girl.”

songs.title: GTG

description.plain:
This song was first released in 2018, before being deleted from all streaming platforms and being re-released on July 8th, 2020, along with a music video.
The first version of the song featured a sample from “Parasite Eve II” in its intro. This sample has been altered in the second release.
